{
  "texts": [
    "Analogously, we get",
    "The new formal monodromy is the product of the partial formal monodromies",
    "We easily check that h S 3 S 2 S 1 = id, so the algorithm provides -as expected -a valid set of Stokes data (h, S 1, S 2, S 3) ∈ M B (Θ, -1) for Θ.",
    "In this case, the Betti moduli spaces M B (Θ, 1) and M B (Θ, -1) both consist of just a point, so the algorithm induces an isomorphism as expected (and there is no symplectic form to be considered). 6.3.",
    "The case of ⟨z 5/3 ⟩ and ⟨w 5/2 ⟩."
  ]
}